This paper is primarily focused on the theoretical analysis of ReLU layers in neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of ReLU layers in computer vision tasks (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces new tools for analyzing neural networks, which could potentially fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
